"{\"uid\": \"tribune.com.pk-story-2483621-goofy-girl-titmus-struggling-to-believe-olympic-gold\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"US  The 23-year-old beat McIntosh and Ledecky to win her second consecutive Olympic 400m freestyle title  Ariarne Titmus said Saturday she can not believe \\\"a goofy girl\\\" from Australia could win back-to-back Olympic 400m freestyle titles, while lavishing praise on rival Katie Ledecky.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 285, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 2, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9481065111736438, \"rank\": 0.02889967614158656, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 25, \"end\": 33, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 0.9999999997153282, \"rank\": 2.8473379036436643e-10, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}, {\"begin\": 106, \"end\": 120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ariarne Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\"}, {\"begin\": 175, \"end\": 184, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9998903632721654, \"rank\": 9.831145305897582e-05, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 271, \"end\": 284, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The down-to-earth 23-year-old held off Canadian teenager Summer McIntosh and American great Ledecky to join Dawn Fraser as the only Australian female swimmer to retain an Olympic crown.\", \"from\": 287, \"to\": 472, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 364, \"end\": 372, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999767574538432, \"rank\": 1.770443496059632e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 395, \"end\": 406, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dawn_Fraser\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dawn Fraser\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dawn_Fraser\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dawn_Fraser\"}, {\"begin\": 419, \"end\": 429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9958362578732088, \"rank\": 0.004176391336946242, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The world record holder was in full control to touch in 3mins 57.49secs ahead of McIntosh (3:58.37) and Ledecky (4:00.86), who faded badly in the final 50m.\", \"from\": 474, \"to\": 630, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I can not believe that's me, to be honest,\\\" she said when asked about what the feat meant.\", \"from\": 632, \"to\": 723, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I look at myself and I am so normal.\", \"from\": 725, \"to\": 762, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I love swimming, and I love getting out and representing my country and having fun.\", \"from\": 763, \"to\": 846, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I hope nobody looks at me any differently.\", \"from\": 848, \"to\": 891, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am just the same old goofy Tassie (Tasmanian) girl out here living out her dream.\", \"from\": 892, \"to\": 975, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I hope it goes to show, anyone can do what they want to do if they work hard and believe in themselves.\", \"from\": 977, \"to\": 1081, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And here I am, from little old Launie (Launceston), a town of 90,000, and I am out here living the dream.\\\"\", \"from\": 1082, \"to\": 1188, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1121, \"end\": 1131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Launceston_Football_Club\", \"score\": 0.9999997517109331, \"rank\": 2.4445477822623113e-07, \"text\": \"Launceston\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Launceston_Football_Club\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Launceston_Football_Club\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Titmus, who dethroned Ledecky in Tokyo, came to France in red-hot form after shattering the 200m world record and swimming the second-quickest 400m ever at the Australian trials.\", \"from\": 1190, \"to\": 1368, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1190, \"end\": 1196, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}, {\"begin\": 1223, \"end\": 1228, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9552843376085127, \"rank\": 0.0468087402687579, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 1238, \"end\": 1244, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9221684340468734, \"rank\": 0.08257551616341204, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1350, \"end\": 1360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9958362578732088, \"rank\": 0.004176391336946242, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Ledecky can never be written off and McIntosh was always going to be a threat after snatching Titmus's world record last year before the Australian took it back.\", \"from\": 1370, \"to\": 1535, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1411, \"end\": 1419, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 0.9999999997153282, \"rank\": 2.8473379036436643e-10, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}, {\"begin\": 1468, \"end\": 1474, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}, {\"begin\": 1511, \"end\": 1521, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9958362578732088, \"rank\": 0.004176391336946242, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, it was all Titmus in Paris, who was near world record pace at the halfway mark and comfortably surged home, with McIntosh winning her first Olympic medal by taking silver.\", \"from\": 1537, \"to\": 1717, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1557, \"end\": 1563, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}, {\"begin\": 1567, \"end\": 1572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999952475265, \"rank\": 4.75247366437345e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1659, \"end\": 1667, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 0.9999999997153282, \"rank\": 2.8473379036436643e-10, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am just happy to get the result for myself, and I am so honoured to be part of the race and be alongside legends like Katie,\\\" Titmus said.\", \"from\": 1719, \"to\": 1860, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1848, \"end\": 1854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I look up to her so much as an athlete, and it is certainly not a rivalry beyond the races.\", \"from\": 1862, \"to\": 1954, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I really respect her as a person.\", \"from\": 1955, \"to\": 1988, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her longevity in the sport.\", \"from\": 1989, \"to\": 2016, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's nice to catch up and have a chat.\\\"\", \"from\": 2017, \"to\": 2056, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's fun racing the best in the world,\\\" she added.\", \"from\": 2058, \"to\": 2109, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It gets the best out of me; it gets the best out of them.\", \"from\": 2110, \"to\": 2168, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I really hope all the hype lived up to the expectation.\", \"from\": 2169, \"to\": 2224, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I really hope that I put on a good show tonight and everyone enjoyed it.\\\"\", \"from\": 2225, \"to\": 2298, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Titmus will also swim the 200m and 800m in Paris.\", \"from\": 2300, \"to\": 2349, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2300, \"end\": 2306, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}, {\"begin\": 2343, \"end\": 2348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999952475265, \"rank\": 4.75247366437345e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky has opted out of the shorter distance, focusing instead on defending her 800m and 1500m titles.\", \"from\": 2351, \"to\": 2454, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"McIntosh is also skipping the 200m free, instead prioritising the 200m and 400m medley and 200m butterfly.\", \"from\": 2456, \"to\": 2562, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2456, \"end\": 2464, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 0.9999999997153282, \"rank\": 2.8473379036436643e-10, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"COMMENTS  Comments are moderated and generally will be posted if they are on-topic and not abusive.\", \"from\": 2564, \"to\": 2663, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For more information, please see ourComments FAQ  This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten,                     redistributed or derived from.\", \"from\": 2665, \"to\": 2823, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Unless otherwise stated, all content is                     copyrighted \\u00a9 2025 The Express Tribune.\", \"from\": 2824, \"to\": 2923, \"entities\": []}]}"